{"ts": "2026-05-18T16:47:34.149849+00:00", "run_key": "HEAL-33616", "kind": "line", "text": "## HEAL-33616 — Lab Order Update Error"}
{"ts": "2026-05-18T16:47:34.149849+00:00", "run_key": "HEAL-33616", "kind": "line", "text": "**Issue:** Salesforce- Lab Order error (J. O'Connell)  "}
{"ts": "2026-05-18T16:47:34.151360+00:00", "run_key": "HEAL-33616", "kind": "line", "text": "**Status:** Escalated to Engineering"}
{"ts": "2026-05-18T16:47:34.152363+00:00", "run_key": "HEAL-33616", "kind": "line", "text": "### Root Cause (Confirmed)"}
{"ts": "2026-05-18T16:47:34.152867+00:00", "run_key": "HEAL-33616", "kind": "line", "text": "Error message: **\"Please insert a category or a product!\"** (error code 400)"}
{"ts": "2026-05-18T16:47:34.154380+00:00", "run_key": "HEAL-33616", "kind": "line", "text": "The \"Update Order\" feature on `Lab_Order__c` is failing because required `Category` or `Product` fields are missing or not being passed to the external lab API. **This is NOT a height/weight validation issue** — the user's original symptom (attempting to update height/weight) is actually a secondary detail. The core problem is the order submission requires category/product data that the two affected records appear to lack."}
{"ts": "2026-05-18T16:47:34.154380+00:00", "run_key": "HEAL-33616", "kind": "line", "text": "### Affected Records"}
{"ts": "2026-05-18T16:47:34.155892+00:00", "run_key": "HEAL-33616", "kind": "line", "text": "- `a47Ql000000O2NFIA0` — J. O'Connell Lab Order (primary, 2026-05-13)"}
{"ts": "2026-05-18T16:47:34.157404+00:00", "run_key": "HEAL-33616", "kind": "line", "text": "- `a47Ql000000M5gzIAC` — Second Lab Order (2026-05-14)  "}
{"ts": "2026-05-18T16:47:34.157404+00:00", "run_key": "HEAL-33616", "kind": "line", "text": "Both records preserved in error state; not re-submitted."}
{"ts": "2026-05-18T16:47:34.158917+00:00", "run_key": "HEAL-33616", "kind": "line", "text": "### Solution"}
{"ts": "2026-05-18T16:47:34.159961+00:00", "run_key": "HEAL-33616", "kind": "line", "text": "Engineering must:"}
{"ts": "2026-05-18T16:47:34.159961+00:00", "run_key": "HEAL-33616", "kind": "line", "text": "1. Inspect the affected records to confirm whether `Category__c` and `Product__c` are null or empty."}
{"ts": "2026-05-18T16:47:34.161473+00:00", "run_key": "HEAL-33616", "kind": "line", "text": "2. Review the \"Update Order\" Flow/Apex code to identify whether it's missing validation, auto-population logic, or correct field mapping to the external API."}
{"ts": "2026-05-18T16:47:34.162979+00:00", "run_key": "HEAL-33616", "kind": "line", "text": "3. Implement fix in Sandbox (data correction vs. code/Flow fix depends on root cause analysis)."}
{"ts": "2026-05-18T16:47:34.162979+00:00", "run_key": "HEAL-33616", "kind": "line", "text": "4. Validate on equivalent test records in Sandbox before promoting to Production."}
